      • load

        public final void load(Node node,
                       WorkflowPersistor parentPersistor,
                       ExecutionMonitor exec,
                       Map<Integer,BufferedDataTable> loadTblRep,
                       HashMap<Integer,ContainerTable> tblRep,
                       WorkflowFileStoreHandlerRepository fileStoreHandlerRepository,
                       WorkflowPersistor.LoadResult loadResult)
                throws IOException,
                       CanceledExecutionException
        Loads content into node instance.
        Parameters:
        node - The target node, used for meta info (#ports, e.g) and to invoke the Node#load(NodePersistor, ExecutionMonitor, LoadResult) on
        parentPersistor - workflow persistor for decryption
        exec - For progress/cancelation
        loadTblRep - The table repository used during load
        tblRep - The table repository for blob handling
        fileStoreHandlerRepository - ...
        loadResult - where to add errors to
        Throws:
        IOException - If files can't be read
        CanceledExecutionException - If canceled
        No public API: not to be referenced by clients
        This method is not intended to be referenced by clients.
        No public API: not to be overriden by clients

                        ReferencedFile nodeDirRef,

        nnc - ...
        settings - ...
        execMon - Used to report progress during saving.
        nodeDirRef - Directory associated with node - will create internals folder in it
        isSaveData - ...
        Throws:
        IOException - If the node file can't be found or read.
        CanceledExecutionException - If the saving has been canceled.
